{"id":20484,"title":"Tetanus in an unvaccinated laborer in Bahrain.","abstract":"Mr. M.D.S., a 27-year-old Indian male, presented with complaints of diffuse body pain and spasms, 7 days after a needle penetrated his right foot at his place of work. He was diagnosed clinically with tetanus. The patient was electively intubated to protect the airway and transferred to an intensive care unit. In addition to his tetanus, he developed multiple hospital-acquired infections. After 34 days, he was successfully extubated and extensive physiotherapy commenced. He was discharged 10 days after extubation. ","date":"2014-05-09","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24656722","annotations":[{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.783697,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Intensive care unit","weight":0.67708,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive_care_unit"},{"name":"Pain","weight":0.670603,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.669249,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Intubation","weight":0.616127,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intubation"},{"name":"Intensive-care medicine","weight":0.491694,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive-care_medicine"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.487161,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Vaccine","weight":0.322139,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccine"},{"name":"Diffusion","weight":0.216664,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffusion"},{"name":"Tracheal intubation","weight":0.215427,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tracheal_intubation"},{"name":"Airway","weight":0.179969,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airway"},{"name":"Tetanus","weight":0.0722222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T